          <!-- Legend + companion notes -->
          <div class="lifecycle-legend">
            <div class="lg-block">
              <span class="lg-h">▶ legend</span>
              <ul>
                <li><span class="lg-swatch ok"></span> hook fires on success</li>
                <li><span class="lg-swatch warn"></span> hook fires on failure / deny</li>
                <li><span class="lg-arr">→</span> synchronous call</li>
                <li><span class="lg-arr d">⇢</span> hook stdin payload (JSON)</li>
                <li><span class="lg-arr l">↻</span> loop back to model</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="lg-block">
              <span class="lg-h">▶ adjacent flows (not shown above)</span>
              <ul>
                <li><code>SessionStart</code> → fires at startup·resume·clear·compact (BEFORE phase ①)</li>
                <li><code>InstructionsLoaded</code> → fires per rule/CLAUDE.md load (during context build, phase ②)</li>
                <li><code>PreCompact</code> → fires when token budget triggers compaction (interrupts the loop)</li>
                <li><code>PostCompact</code> → fires after summarizer trims; then <code>SessionStart(source:compact)</code> re-runs</li>
                <li><code>FileChanged</code> · <code>CwdChanged</code> · <code>WorktreeCreate/Remove</code> → orthogonal system events</li>
                <li><code>SessionEnd</code> → fires when the session terminates</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="lg-block">
              <span class="lg-h">▶ gotchas worth bookmarking</span>
              <ul>
                <li><code>PostToolUse</code> = tool <b>success</b>. Bash pipes mask exit codes — use <code>PostToolUseFailure</code> for non-zero.</li>
                <li><code>PreToolUse</code> exit <code>2</code> blocks the tool AND surfaces stderr to the agent. Only blocking hook.</li>
                <li>Sub-agent's own loop has its own <code>PreToolUse</code>/<code>PostToolUse</code> calls — they share <code>session_id</code>.</li>
                <li>Hook payload diverges on failure: <code>.error</code> top-level instead of <code>.tool_response</code>.</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>

        </article>
